      "id": "d60db426-2ba0-47ec-af78-75b327b8e604",
      "name": "Code in JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔄 Workflow Overview\n\n**📥 Email Ingestion & Deduplication**\nGmail polls every minute for new emails. When one arrives, the full message is fetched including attachments. The subject line is checked — if it does not contain \"Police Report\" the workflow stops immediately. The email thread ID is then checked against Google Sheets to see if it was already processed. If it was, the workflow stops to prevent duplicate processing. If it is new, the UUID and sender email are logged into the KPI tracker and the flow continues.\n\n**📄 PDF Extraction via LlamaParse**\nThe police report PDF attachment is uploaded to LlamaParse using the agentic tier for high-accuracy OCR. Since LlamaParse processes files asynchronously, a wait node pauses execution and then polls the job status. If the status is not yet COMPLETED the workflow loops back to wait. Once completed, the extracted markdown is ready for AI processing.\n\n**🤖 AI Extraction & Clio Lookup**\nThe extracted markdown is passed to Google Gemini along with the original PDF filename. The filename is critical — it identifies the plaintiff (name before _v_) and defendant (name after _v_). Gemini returns a clean structured JSON with all required case fields. The JSON is then parsed and used to look up the matching Clio Contact by name, which in turn retrieves the associated Matter ID.\n\n**📋 Paralegal Verification Handoff**\nAll extracted fields along with the original PDF are sent to the Swans verification app, which generates a unique form URL for the paralegal to review. An approval email is sent to the paralegal with a direct link to the form. Once sent, the case row in Google Sheets is updated with the form link, Matter ID, and status set to Pending — awaiting the paralegal's approve or reject action.",
        "height": 752,
        "width": 512,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1216,
        -64
      ],
